//! 1. Start with varimax rotation
//! 2. Raise absolute values of loadings to a power (preserving signs)
//! 3. Use regression to find oblique transformation
//! 4. Normalize the result
//! 
//! # References
//! 
//! Hendrickson, A. E., & White, P. O. (1964). Promax: A quick method for rotation
//! to oblique simple structure. British Journal of Statistical Psychology, 17(1), 65-70.

