//! Principal Component Analysis (PCA) module
//! 
//! This module provides PCA functionality with support for various
//! component selection methods, rotation techniques, and diagnostic tools.
//! 
//! # R multivarious Package Compatibility
//! 
//! This module implements the PCA functionality from the R multivarious package,
//! providing equivalent functionality to:
//! 
//! - `pca()` - Main PCA fitting function
//! - `bi_projector` - Bidirectional projection (scores/loadings)
//! - `project()` - Transform new data using fitted PCA
//! - `reconstruct()` - Inverse transform from component space
//! - `transpose()` - Variable-space PCA
//! - `residuals()` - Reconstruction residuals
//! - `scores()` - Get component scores
//! - `loadings()` / `components()` - Get variable loadings
//! - `sdev()` - Standard deviations of components
//! 
//! # Additional Features from R multivarious
//! 
//! - **Permutation Testing**: Vitale et al. (2017) methodology for component significance
//! - **Component Rotation**: Varimax, Quartimax, Equamax, Promax
//! - **Outlier Detection**: Hotelling T², Q-residuals
//! - **Diagnostics**: Variable/sample contributions, influence measures
//! - **Component Selection**: Kaiser criterion, elbow method, variance thresholds
//! 
//! # Example Usage
//! 
//! ```
//! use multivarious::pca::{Pca, PcaBuilder};
//! use ndarray::array;
//! 
//! // Create data
//! let data = array![
//!     [2.5, 2.4],
//!     [0.5, 0.7],
//!     [2.2, 2.9],
//!     [1.9, 2.2],
//!     [3.1, 3.0],
//! ];
//! 
//! // Fit PCA (like R's pca() or prcomp())
//! let mut pca = PcaBuilder::new()
//!     .use_correlation(false)  // Use covariance matrix
//!     .n_components(2)
//!     .build();
//! 
//! pca.fit(&data).unwrap();
//! 
//! // Access results like R multivarious
//! let scores = pca.transform(&data).unwrap();  // project()
//! let loadings = pca.components().unwrap();    // loadings()
//! let sdev = pca.standard_deviations();        // sdev()
//! let var_explained = pca.explained_variance_ratio(); // summary()
//! ```

